  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "python-jwt security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for python-jwt is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "rm -f tests/test_jwks_client.py  -m pytest %endif\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nPyJWT is a JSON Web Token implementation in Python. Prior to 2.12.0, PyJWT does not validate the crit (Critical) Header Parameter defined in RFC 7515 §4.1.11. When a JWS token contains a crit array listing extensions that PyJWT does not understand, the library accepts the token instead of rejecting it. This violates the MUST requirement in the RFC. This vulnerability is fixed in 2.12.0.(CVE-2026-32597)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for python-jwt is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "python-jwt",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
